	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 13th 7:40 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=68492"><span id=" ">necrro</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">66 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Good [4.28]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Last night I purchased an item not on this site called a WORM EATEN SKULL CHARM.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has some decent stats (HP, Mana, Saves) and Aura of Health (Worn). I ran several tests on my toon and here are the results: <br/><br/>1. It is not a right click effect (as I presume a Buff would have to be) <br/><br/>2. It does not add any more HP when worn than what is already on it (HP +20 I think). <br/><br/>3. I discovered through testing that it has a +1 regen effect to it when worn that stacks with at least Zlandicar's Heart (which I have). <br/><br/>At 58, with Z-Heart and no innate regen AA yet, I had a standing regen of 8pts per tick without Skull Charm and 9 hp per tick with. I tested this several times. 11 hp per tick sitting without Skull Charm and 12 hp per tick with. <br/><br/>My inescapable conclusion: Aura of Health (worn) = Regen +1 which when discovered will most likely drive the price of this Neck item up. Im keeping it on.<br/> <br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Necrro Mancer<br/>66nd Warlock of Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
